WEBVTT

p01
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.327
Open the Customers list.

p02
00:00:01.719 --> 00:00:03.405
Notice how the page stacks up.

p03
00:00:03.689 --> 00:00:05.034
Summary numbers on top, insight cards in the middle, the table underneath.

p04
00:00:05.264 --> 00:00:07.714
Every list in WashCentral is built this way,

p05
00:00:08.150 --> 00:00:15.003
so the shape you learn right here is the shape you'll read on every screen after it.

p06
00:00:15.470 --> 00:00:17.212
Start at the four tiles up top.

p07
00:00:17.634 --> 00:00:20.614
They summarize the whole customer base in one glance:

p08
00:00:21.014 --> 00:00:23.551
how many customers, how many active members, how many at risk, how many prospects.

p09
00:00:23.899 --> 00:00:31.360
Read these before the table, because they frame everything the rows are about to show you.

p10
00:00:31.830 --> 00:00:33.725
Below the tiles, three cards.

p11
00:00:34.249 --> 00:00:35.860
One tracks growth over the year, one shows how members split across plans,

p12
00:00:36.129 --> 00:00:38.370
one rates overall health from low to high.

p13
00:00:38.719 --> 00:00:41.249
It's the trend and the risk at a glance,

p14
00:00:41.798 --> 00:00:46.848
so you catch the story before you ever sort a column.

p15
00:00:47.380 --> 00:00:48.699
Now the list card itself.

p16
00:00:49.434 --> 00:00:53.521
Its title and the small label above it tell you which dataset you're looking at.

p17
00:00:54.464 --> 00:00:56.502
Off to the right sit the action buttons.

p18
00:00:57.045 --> 00:01:00.445
Two of them, Delete and Add Customer, change records,

p19
00:01:00.845 --> 00:01:03.600
so we leave them alone today and just note where they live.

p20
00:01:04.130 --> 00:01:05.477
Look at the search box.

p21
00:01:06.006 --> 00:01:08.978
The grey placeholder inside it isn't decoration.

p22
00:01:09.561 --> 00:01:12.175
It spells out every field the search will match: name, plate, email, location, plan.

p23
00:01:12.637 --> 00:01:21.798
When you're not sure how a list can be searched, that hint answers it for you.

p24
00:01:22.400 --> 00:01:23.931
Next to it, the Filters button.

p25
00:01:24.412 --> 00:01:25.755
Watch the little number on it.

p26
00:01:26.099 --> 00:01:29.460
Zero means nothing is filtered and you're seeing the full list.

p27
00:01:29.826 --> 00:01:35.600
Anything higher means someone narrowed it,

p28
00:01:36.035 --> 00:01:36.200
which is the first thing to check when a customer swears a record is missing.

p29
00:01:36.200 --> 00:01:37.796
Run your eye across the headers.

p30
00:01:38.139 --> 00:01:46.109
Six columns, and every one sorts,

p31
00:01:47.030 --> 00:01:50.877
so you can order by plan, by join date, by monthly price, whatever the question needs.

p32
00:01:51.186 --> 00:01:52.080
The checkboxes down the left let you pick rows for the Delete button.

p33
00:01:52.514 --> 00:01:52.720
We won't check any.

p34
00:01:52.720 --> 00:01:54.400
Look at the coloured chips in a row.

p35
00:01:55.377 --> 00:01:58.145
The plan chip names what the customer pays for;

p36
00:01:58.861 --> 00:02:02.715
the status chip is green for active, grey for inactive.

p37
00:02:03.571 --> 00:02:09.710
Colour does the work, so you read a customer's standing in a glance instead of parsing text.

p38
00:02:09.710 --> 00:02:10.388
Drop to the footer.

p39
00:02:11.134 --> 00:02:16.005
The rows-per-page control and the page arrows are how you travel a big table.

p40
00:02:16.472 --> 00:02:17.685
And these are big: this list runs past a million and a half migrated records.

p41
00:02:17.997 --> 00:02:21.554
The tiles said two thousand, the pages say millions.

p42
00:02:22.182 --> 00:02:29.520
Both are right, they're just counting different things.

p43
00:02:29.520 --> 00:02:30.840
Now switch to Gift Cards.

p44
00:02:31.148 --> 00:02:33.073
Same page, different subject.

p45
00:02:33.444 --> 00:02:36.852
Tiles across the top, three insight cards, then the list.

p46
00:02:37.266 --> 00:02:42.252
The words changed to cards and balances,

p47
00:02:42.453 --> 00:02:43.430
but the skeleton is identical to the one you just learned.

p48
00:02:43.920 --> 00:02:44.290
That's the whole point.

p49
00:02:44.290 --> 00:02:45.286
Read the controls here.

p50
00:02:45.589 --> 00:02:51.306
The search hint, the columns, and the rows-per-page choices, twenty-five, fifty, or a hundred,

p51
00:02:51.510 --> 00:02:53.116
all match the Customer List.

p52
00:02:53.579 --> 00:02:58.186
If the table reads couldn't load records, that's a data hiccup, not an empty list,

p53
00:02:58.407 --> 00:03:01.700
and the dashes in the tiles are the same story.

p54
00:03:01.700 --> 00:03:02.123
That's the pattern.

p55
00:03:02.543 --> 00:03:03.550
KPI strip, insight cards, search and filters,

p56
00:03:03.850 --> 00:03:09.657
sortable columns with chips, and a pager at the bottom.

p57
00:03:10.141 --> 00:03:13.194
Learn it on these two lists and you've learned it everywhere.

p58
00:03:13.697 --> 00:03:18.800
From here on, every list in WashCentral reads the same, no matter which module you're in.

